---
description: Enforce JSDoc for all TS symbols in the Obsidian plugin.
globs:
  - "**/*.ts"
  - "**/*.tsx"
alwaysApply: false
---

Use JSDoc (/** … */) for all functions, classes, methods, interfaces, and exported constants.

- Keep a one-line summary; add detail if helpful.
- Include `@param` for every parameter and `@returns` when non-void.
- Add `@throws` if errors may be thrown.
- Prefer clear, Google-style phrasing but in **JSDoc syntax**.
- If a signature changes, update the doc block to match (names, types, returns).
- Do not change code logic when adding or editing docs.
